President Trump spoke at a Special Session on the Digital Economy during the G20 Summit in Osaka, Japan. He highlighted the importance of the digital economy in driving economic growth and emphasized the need for the free flow of data, privacy protection, intellectual property rights, access to capital, and innovation. Trump expressed the United States' commitment to sustaining this approach to digital trade and working with like-minded partners to advance these priorities. He also emphasized the importance of ensuring the resilience and security of 5G networks. Trump stated that the United States opposes data localization policies that restrict digital trade flows and violate privacy and intellectual property protections. He called for a future of digital trade that empowers all people and promotes an open, fair, and market-based digital economy.